{{Infobox sport tournament |year = 2011 |name = Austria's Strongest Man |image = |location = Austria, various locations |establishment = 1989 |format = Multi-event competition |purse = |month_played = <!--Use if still played--> |final_year= |current_champion = {{flagicon|Austria}} [[Martin Wildauer]] |final_champion = }}
'''Austria's Strongest Man''' is an annual [[Strongman (strength athlete)|strongman]] contest consisting of exclusively [[Austria]]n strength athletes.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.davidhorne-gripmaster.com/strongmanresults.html David Horne's World of Grip<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The event was established in 1989, the inaugural winner was [[Manfred Hoeberl]] who would go on to win the title a total of 7 times.<ref name=autogenerated1 />
