'''Brooklyn''' was an Italian professional [[cycling team]] that existed from 1970 to 1977.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dreher (1970)|url=http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.eu/pelotons/equipes.php?q=7685|language=French|publisher=Mémoire du cyclisme|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brooklin (1977)|url=http://www.memoire-du-cyclisme.eu/pelotons/equipes.php?q=8187|language=French|publisher=Mémoire du cyclisme|accessdate=1 February 2017}}</ref> It was a mainly a [[Classic cycle races|one-day classics]] team and featured riders such as [[Roger De Vlaeminck]], who won [[Paris–Roubaix]] four times. For the first three seasons it was sponsored by the Italian beer Dreher, and then for the following seasons by Italy's Brooklyn Chewing Gum.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hays|first1=Elizabeth|title=Brooklyn gum's here - from Italy|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/archives/boroughs/brooklyn-gum-italy-article-1.630278|accessdate=1 February 2017|work=[[New York Daily News]]|date=27 July 2005}}</ref>

The documentary film ''[[A Sunday in Hell]]'' features the team during the [[1976 Paris–Roubaix]].

