{{Infobox_Judo technique |name =Harai tsurikomi ashi |image = Harai-tsurikomi-ashi.jpg |image_size = 175px |alt = |caption = |class =[[Nage-waza]] |sub_class =[[List_of_judo_techniques#Ashi-waza_.28.E8.B6.B3.E6.8A.80.29:_foot_throwing_techniques|Ashi-waza]] |grip = |back_up = |follow_up = |targets = |counter = |kodokan =Yes |romaji =Harai-tsurikomi ashi |japanese =払釣込足 |english =Lift-pull foot sweep }}{{nihongo|'''Harai Tsurikomi Ashi'''|払釣込足}} is one of the original 40 [[Throw (grappling)|throws]] of [[Judo]] as developed by [[Jigoro Kano]]. It belongs to the third group, [[Judo Lists#Sankyo|Sankyo]], of the traditional throwing list, Gokyo (no waza), of Kodokan Judo. It is also part of the current 67 Throws of Kodokan Judo. It is classified as a foot technique, [[Judo technique|Ashi-waza]].
