{{Infobox stadium | name = Mayor Vitaliano D. Agan Coliseum | nickname = | fullname = | former_names = Zamboanga City Coliseum | image = [[File:Mayor Vitaliano D. Agan (Zamboanga City) Coliseum.jpg|220px|]] | caption = Inside the arena | location = Don Alfaro Street, Tetuan, [[Zamboanga City]], [[Philippines]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2002 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Local Government of Zamboanga | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = [[Philippine peso|₱]]130 million | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 10,000 <ref>http://www.newsflash.org/2002/02/pe/pe002197.htm</ref> | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = [[Zamboanga Valientes]] (2018-present) }}
The '''Mayor Vitaliano D. Agan Coliseum''' <ref>https://drive.google.com/file/d/0BzjWd8iSYqqecVF0Y3ItZmluQlk/view</ref> is an indoor multi-purpose sports arena located in the [[Zamboanga City|City of Zamboanga]] in the island of [[Mindanao]], [[Philippines]]. It is one of the biggest air-conditioned coliseum in Mindanao that can accommodate up to 10,000 spectators. It has also been the home of the [[Philippine Basketball Association|PBA]] in the Zamboanga Peninsula.
==Events== ===Inauguration=== Zamboanga City Coliseum in Barangay Tetuan, was the center of the grand celebration of Dia de Zamboanga last February 26, 2002. It was formally Inaugurated by President Gloria Macapagal-Aroyo
===Regular events=== The coliseum is one of the venues the [[Philippine Basketball Association]] in the Zamboanga Peninsula for the past decade.
It also a regular host of boxing events in the city and is currently the host of festival events, such us the Hermosa Street Dance Festival & Cheer Dance Competitions
