{{Infobox stadium |stadium_name = Pyunik Stadium |image = FC Pyunik Stadium, Yerevan.jpg |image_size = |caption = |location = [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]] |built = 2004 |opened = 2004 |owner = [[Ruben Hayrapetyan]] |operator = [[FC Pyunik]] |seating_capacity = 780 |surface = [[artificial turf]] (since 2016) |dimensions = 105 x 68 meters |tenants = [[FC Pyunik#Pyunik-2|Pyunik-2]] }}
'''Pyunik Stadium''' ({{lang-hy|Փյունիկ Մարզադաշտ}}), is an [[all-seater stadium|all-seater]] [[association football|football]] [[stadium]] located on 7 Masis street, [[Kentron District]], [[Yerevan]], [[Armenia]].<ref>[http://old.ffa.am/am/teams/fcpyunik/ FC Pyunik at the FFA site]</ref> It was built and opened in 2004. With a capacity of 770 seats, the stadium is home to Pyunik-2 of the [[Armenian First League]].
==Overview== The stadium was opened in 2004 as part of the [[Pyunik Training Centre]] which was formerly known as the Kilikia Sports Complex.
In 2016, the stadium was renovated and the pitch was covered with an up-to-date artificial turf.<ref>[http://www.ffa.am/hy/1475136313 News stadiums in Armenia and Artsakh]</ref>
A large fitness center, a tennis complex and a small hotel are found adjacent to the stadium.
The stadium is the regular home of the [[Armenian First League]] side [[FC Pyunik#Pyunik-2|Pyunik-2]]. It is sometimes used by [[FC Pyunik|Pyunik]] as well for their [[Armenian Premier League]] matches. In 2017-18, the stadium has also served as the home venue of [[Artsakh FC]] at the [[Armenian First League]].
