A '''stop-and-go''' or a '''hitch-and-go''' is a [[Route (gridiron football)|route]] run by a [[wide receiver|receiver]] in [[American football]]. It is a combination of a fake [[Curl (route)|curl]] (or hitch) followed by a go (or [[fly route]]).<ref>http://amfootball.isport.com/amfootball-guides/common-football-pass-routes</ref>
